---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Agent Post-training Roadmap">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Roadmap</p>
    <h1>Agent Post-training Roadmap</h1>
    <p>
      The goal here is not to write another long note. It is to turn your existing material into a durable top-level route that new content can attach to.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-split">
    <article class="content-card">
      <h2>Suggested core route</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Start with post-training basics: SFT, reward models, RLHF, DPO, and GRPO.</li>
        <li>Then move into agents: planning, tool use, state feedback, memory, and environment interaction.</li>
        <li>Finish with engineering views: TRL, OpenRLHF, verl, rollouts, and reward wiring.</li>
      </ol>
    </article>

    <article class="content-card">
      <h2>Material already attached</h2>
      <ul class="link-list">
        <li><a href="/archive/html/pytorch-llm-post-training.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">PyTorch LLM Post-Training Primer</a></li>
        <li><a href="/archive/html/deepseek-r1-report.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">DeepSeek-R1 Technical Report</a></li>
        <li><a href="/archive/html/fireworks-rlvr.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Fireworks RLVR / GRPO Reading</a></li>
        <li><a href="/archive/html/post-training-engineering.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">TRL / OpenRLHF / verl Engineering Route</a></li>
        <li><a href="/archive/markdown/agent-post-training-roadmap.md" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Original Markdown Notes</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <article class="content-card">
      <h2>How to continue from here</h2>
      <p>
        New content should land in a fixed slot: concepts, paper reading, engineering route, or experiment log. That keeps the homepage stable instead of turning it into a file dump.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
